<html><body><p>Here are drawings from a protest in Waihi and Aucland.
</p><div>I love my new landscape sketchbook - the pages are long! These drawings are all in my A4 visual diary.</div>

 



 



 



 



 



 



<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-816" style="color: #333333; font-style: normal; line-height: 24px; margin-top: 0.4em;" title="20120818-112141.jpg" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112141-e1345265357222.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="960">



Sketch of Janelle protesting across the street. I held my sign with my legs and just sketched, multitasking. I did several drawings of Janell in my sketchbook - and in return she drew a portrait of herself for me. <a href="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112350.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112350.jpg" alt="20120818-112350.jpg"></a>



A merge of the 'Fuck the system' badge attached to Janelles jeans and the massive hole at Waihi - Mining! The view was incredible - shame I didn't have my normal pencils - only this yellow. The line is much heavier than pencil.



<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-815" style="color: #333333; font-size: 15.555556297302246px; font-style: normal; line-height: 26.666667938232422px; margin-top: 0.4em;" title="20120818-112059.jpg" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112059-e1345265273836.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="960">



Portrait that Janelle drew in my book during the car drive up to Auckland. I always like it when someone gives me a piece of their own creative lives. <a href="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112359.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112359.jpg" alt="20120818-112359.jpg"></a>



 



Henderson drawing. This was at the train station - observing an intersection below. Aucklands been fun to explore with my sketchbook.

<a href="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112205.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-817" title="20120818-112205.jpg" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112205-e1345265243657.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="960"></a>The drive up north with Gary. I tried to fill in perspective - by using both the view outside the car and the interal of the car. Roads were a large focus of this - attempting to capture the scale and rotation. <a href="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112044.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-814" title="20120818-112044.jpg" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112044-e1345265302334.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="960"></a>Candles. Where I stayed with Gary. This is the view from the kitchen table- Again working with perspective - candles in foreground and shelf in background.

<a href="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112035.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-813" title="20120818-112035.jpg" src="http://artcontrol.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/20120818-112035-e1345265329306.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="960"></a>Where me and Gary stopped for the break on the trip. It was a beautiful view so I did a quick sketch. I included someones van for added scale.</body></html>